My first metal piece. ‘Relating’. This piece is an act of grieving the loss of a loved one. It is that feeling of being stripped bare, pierced through by cold, outward objects,  and of trying to get used to the new taste of steel deep within you. 
But the new tougher skin  has grown and patched the wound with the stitches —  the irreversible course of life took over and started the process of creating anew.

Aluminum, ropes, 175x175cm.

GUCCI COSMOS EXHIBITION
SHANGHAI until June 25. 

So much love in my heart ♥️ - I’ve been working with the most talented people and we just opened the Gucci Cosmos Exhibition in Shanghai, where I directed all the video art.
Inspired by the idea of ‘Cathedral Thinking’ the exhibition portrays how the ideas of one generation have been expanded upon by the next to create the myth of the House, beating through time and only possible through that intangible collaboration.

GUCCI COSMOS EXHIBITION LONDON 11 OCT - 31 DEC 2023

Before the upcoming @gucci Cosmos exhibition in London, that I’m thrilled to work on too with the best team, I will be sharing the captivating rooms from our previous Shanghai edition, a mesmerizing collaboration with Es Devlin. 

TWO: visitors are faced with a pair of monumental 10-metre-tall white statues. Standing as if guarding the entrance to an ancient temple, they symbolize the House’s trailblazing belief in unisex fashion and its ability to shift societal ideas and behaviour. Projected onto the statues’ ‘blank canvases’ in a loop are images of men’s and women’s suits from Gucci’s past and present. These include the celebrated red velvet suit created for both men and women by Tom Ford in 1996; one striking Frida Giannini-designed checked suit with cinched waists; and designs by Alessandro Michele, such as his sparklingly floral unisex versions from 2016 and one from his ‘Twinsburg’ collection, shown in 2022.

Thank you @gucci and @beniaminomarini ♥️
